<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Section 9.2 of the Zend_Framework manual, in the example code underneath subsection heading, "Examples of specifying no columns", the code sample reads:</p>

&lt;?php 
// Build this query: 
//   SELECT p."product_id", p."product_name" 
//   FROM "products" AS p JOIN "line_items" AS l 
//     ON p.product_id = l.product_id 
$select = $db-&gt;select() 
    -&gt;from(array('p' =&gt; 'products'), 
        array('product_id', 'product_name')) 
    -&gt;join(array('l' =&gt; 'line_items'), 
        'p.product_id = l.product_id' 
        array() ); // empty list of columns 
?&gt;

<p>It should have a comma after the 'p.product_id = l.product_id' stanza. Perhaps, also trivial, bolding the 'array()' notation would also facilitate understanding of this 'empty array' concept to new users.</p>

<p>Thank you.</p>

